T1  - A specification test of the Heckscher-Ohlin theory
AU  - Staiger, Robert W.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 1
SP  - 129
EP  - 141
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(88)90008-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199688900086
AB  - Under strong assumptions, the Heckscher-Ohlin model predicts not only that factor endowment differences alone determine trade patterns, but that they do so in a particularly simple way: the factor content of trade should be a linear function of national and world factor endowments. The evident empirical shortcomings of this simple relationship need not, however, imply the more general empirical failure of endowment-based trade theories. This paper provides empirical evidence consistent with a more general endowment-based model, by showing that the strong Heckscher-Ohlin relationship excludes important additional channels through which factor endowments affect the pattern of trade.
