AB  - The paper presents a general equilibrium model in which an autarky allocation is Pareto superior to a free trade allocation. In this environment, agents' decisions regarding their choices of jobs and consumption are affected by wage and price fluctuations associated with these two regimes. It is also found that the free trade equilibrium is unique and unstable when it is Pareto inferior to autarky. These extreme results point out the crucial significance of the incomplete markets assumption in true general equilibrium settings.
